  }, "Amanda, Designer of Connect the Stars"), mdx("p", null, "My most fateful play-testing session was with my friend David. David wasn\u2019t particularly good at movie trivia, so they\u2019d often ask their partner Amanda for help. Amanda, who happens to be a professional designer, turned out to be a natural at the game."), mdx("p", null, "I thought about how much Amanda \u201Cgot\u201D the game right away and understood its appeal. In mid-August, while I was on a trip with my family, I asked her to help me redesign the game. I wanted to work on Connect the Stars as soon as I was back from my trip, and figured that, if she said yes, she would need to find some free time and take a while to put things together. To my surprise, she put together some mocks the same evening that I asked her for help! I had spotty internet during all this, so it was only after I got back home that I looked at the designs and loved them right away."), mdx("p", null, "The rest of the development of Connect the Stars was on-and-off over the course of almost two months, during which Amanda and I would bounce ideas off each other and polish the design over and over again. Amanda crafted the website\u2019s appearance to have a refined, awards-ceremony vibe. The colours are now way better, there\u2019s now so much more iconography, and everything looks classy. An aesthetic totally opposite of what I had envisioned, but vastly superior."), mdx("p", null, "Amanda also made the logo. We went through a lot of options, as pictured here:"), mdx("p", null, mdx("span", {
